text: Manhay () is a municipality of Wallonia located in the province of Luxembourg, Belgium. On 1 January 2007 the municipality, which covers 119.81 km², had 3,185 inhabitants, giving a population density of 26.6 inhabitants per km². The municipality consists of the following districts: Dochamps, Grandménil, Harre, Malempré, Odeigne and Vaux-Chavanne (town centre). ==See also== * List of protected heritage sites in Manhay ==References== ==External links== * Category:Municipalities of Luxembourg (Belgium)
